---
id: org.dxos.plugin.map
name: MapPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

An interactive geospatial mapping plugin for `DXOS` Composer.
Renders table records that contain latitude/longitude coordinates as pins on a zoomable map or 3-D globe.
Supports creating map objects backed by a view over any ECHO dataset, with a geolocation field selector for automatic marker placement.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`       |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`       |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`       |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`  |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`         |

## Types

```mdl
type GeoPoint
  desc: A geographic coordinate pair stored in GeoJSON [lng, lat] order.
  fields:
    lat: number
    lng: number
```

```mdl
type MapViewType
  literals: map | globe
```

```mdl
type Map
  desc: An ECHO object representing a named geospatial map, optionally linked to a view over a dataset.
  fields:
    name?: string
    view?: Ref<View>            # optional pivot view that drives marker data
    center?: GeoPoint           # last saved viewport centre
    zoom?: number               # last saved zoom level
    coordinates?: GeoPoint[]    # static coordinate list (no view required)
```

```mdl
type CreateMap
  desc: Input schema for the create-object dialog.
  fields:
    name?: string
    typename?: string           # schema typename to use as pin source
    locationFieldName?: string  # field on the selected typename that holds a GeoPoint
```

```mdl
type MapState
  desc: Transient viewport state held in a plugin-scoped Atom.
  fields:
    type: MapViewType
    center?: GeoPoint
    zoom?: number
```

## Components

```mdl
component MapArticle
  desc: Primary article/section surface; renders the map or globe for a Map object.
  props:
    role: article | section
    subject: Map
    type: MapViewType
    center?: GeoPoint
    zoom?: number
  state:
    center: GeoPoint            # controlled from parent via onChange
    zoom: number
  slots:
    toolbar?: ReactNode
  actions:
    toggleView()               # switches between map and globe
  emits:
    onChange(center: GeoPoint, zoom: number)
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────────┐
    │ [toolbar slot]              │
    ├─────────────────────────────┤
    │                             │
    │   MapControl / GlobeControl │
    │   (markers from view)       │
    │                             │
    └─────────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component MapViewEditor
  desc: Object-properties panel for picking the dataset view and geolocation field.
  props:
    object: Map
  state:
    typename?: string           # currently selected schema typename
    locationFieldName?: string  # selected GeoPoint field on chosen typename
  slots:
    footer?: ReactNode
  emits:
    onChange(map: Map)
  layout: |
    ┌───────────────────────────┐
    │ Pin type selector         │
    │ Location property picker  │
    │ [footer slot]             │
    └───────────────────────────┘
```

## Operations

```mdl
op createMap
  desc: Creates a new Map ECHO object, optionally with a view derived from a dataset.
  input:
    name?: string
    typename?: string
    locationFieldName?: string
    target?: Space | Collection
    targetNodeId?: string
  output: Map
  effects: [echo:write]
  note: |
    When typename is provided a ViewModel is constructed first, producing the
    backing View; the Map is then created referencing that view.
```

```mdl
op toggleMapView
  desc: Toggles the active MapState between map and globe rendering modes.
  input:
  output: void
  note: Mutates the plugin-scoped MapState Atom in place; no ECHO write.
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Map Creation

  req F-1.1: User can create a Map object from the space or collection create menu.
  req F-1.2:
    when: typename is provided in the creation form
    then: a ViewModel is created for that schema; Map.view references it
  req F-1.3:
    when: locationFieldName is provided
    then: the View's pivotFieldId is set to the corresponding field id
  req F-1.4: A Map with no view can still display static coordinates from Map.coordinates.
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Geospatial Rendering

  req F-2.1:
    when: a Map object is opened as article or section
    then: MapArticle renders in the current MapState.type mode (map or globe)
  req F-2.2:
    when: Map.view is set
    then: the plugin queries the linked dataset and converts rows to GeoMarker pins
  req F-2.3:
    when: a row's GeoPoint field is absent or malformed
    then: that row is silently omitted from the marker list
  req F-2.4:
    when: MapState.type === globe
    then: GlobeControl is rendered instead of MapControl
```

```mdl
feat F-3: View Toggle

  req F-3.1:
    when: the toggle operation is invoked
    then: MapState.type flips between map and globe
  req F-3.2: Toggle state is plugin-scoped; all open map surfaces reflect the change.
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Object Properties

  req F-4.1:
    when: Map object properties are opened
    then: MapViewEditor is rendered in the properties panel
  req F-4.2: User can change the source typename and geolocation field from the editor.
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Blueprint

  req F-5.1: MapPlugin contributes a Blueprint that enables AI to create and update maps.
  req F-5.2: The blueprint instructions describe the plugin's geospatial capabilities.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Create map without view
  given: a space with no external schema
  when: user creates a Map with only a name
  then:
    - Map object created with Map.view === undefined
    - MapArticle renders an empty map with no markers
```

```mdl
test T-2: Create map with view
  given: a schema typename exists with a GeoPoint field 'location'
  when: user creates a Map selecting that typename and 'location' as locationFieldName
  then:
    - ViewModel created; Map.view references the resulting View
    - markers derived from rows appear on the map
```

```mdl
test T-3: Toggle map/globe
  given: MapArticle is rendered in map mode
  when: toggleMapView operation is invoked
  then:
    - MapState.type === globe
    - GlobeControl is rendered
```

```mdl
test T-4: Malformed GeoPoint omitted
  given: a Map view with 3 rows; 1 row has a null GeoPoint
  when: MapArticle renders
  then:
    - exactly 2 markers appear
    - no error is thrown
```

```mdl
test T-5: Object properties editor shown
  given: a Map object is selected
  when: the object properties panel opens
  then: MapViewEditor is rendered with the current typename and field selections pre-filled
```

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

Extension block types used in this document are defined below using
the core `ext` primitive — the only construct the base language provides.

```mdl
ext type
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0
  desc: A named data structure with typed fields and optional literals.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    fields?: FieldMap
    literals?: UnionList
    extends?: TypeRef[]
```

```mdl
ext feat
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0
  desc: A named feature grouping one or more requirements.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    req: RequirementList
  nesting: self
```

```mdl
ext test
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0
  desc: An acceptance scenario expressed as given / when / then steps.
  fields:
    given?: Step | Step[]
    when?: Step | Step[]
    then: Step | Step[]
    tags?: TagList
```

```mdl
ext component
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0
  desc: A UI component with props, internal state, slots, actions, and events.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    props?: FieldMap
    state?: FieldMap
    slots?: FieldMap
    actions?: ActionMap
    emits?: EventMap
    layout?: CodeBlock
```

```mdl
ext op
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0
  desc: |
    A named operation with typed inputs, outputs, and declared errors.
    Pure ops have no effects or requires. Effectful ops declare both.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    input?: FieldMap
    output?: TypeExpr
    errors?: ErrorMap
    effects?: EffectList
    requires?: ServiceList
    note?: Prose
```
